			<note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" place="foot" n="2" xml:id="foot_0"><p>In the literature, sometimes classes are also referred to as labels but these should not be confused with the labels/identifiers.</p></note>
			<note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" place="foot" n="3" xml:id="foot_1"><p>The following definitions assume skolemised blank nodes, i.e., transformed into IRIs.</p></note>
			<note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" place="foot" n="4" xml:id="foot_2"><p>In RDF KGs, the class of a node is provided with the predicate rdf:type.</p></note>
			<note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" place="foot" n="5" xml:id="foot_3"><p>There is another version of LMKG with unsupervised learning, however, its performance was inferior in comparison to its supervised counterpart. Therefore, we focus only on the supervised setting of LMKG.</p></note>
